translations: n.流浪者；特种战线（ranger 的复数）

sentences.sentence: Rangers were playing in front of their home crowd.
sentences.translation: 巡游者队在主场观众面前比赛。

sentences.sentence: Every year, tens of thousands of kids aged 3 to 13 become Junior Rangers in different national parks across America.
sentences.translation: 每年，成千上万3到13岁的孩子在全美各地的国家公园成为初级护林员。

sentences.sentence: Three rangers and five Congolese soldiers were killed.
sentences.translation: 三名护林员和五名刚果士兵阵亡。
